News: ['The key support level for Nifty is placed at 11,212.57, followed by 11,156.13. If the index moves up, key resistance levels to watch out for are 11,357.47 and 11,445.93.', 'As long as the Nifty sustains above 11,036 levels on the closing basis, one can retain a positive stance, Mazhar Mohammad says.', 'Vinod Nair, Head of Research at Geojit Financial Services said that the funds allocated by IMF and easing monetary measures are marginally supporting global markets but India is underperforming due to coronavirus cases.', 'The most active stocks included State Bank of India, YES Bank, Reliance Industries, Indiabulls Housing Finance and IRCTC.', 'Technically, the market is trying to find a bottom after a vertical fall but there is a need for some kind of relief on the Coronavirus front for the market to witness any relief rally.', 'All sectoral indices, barring Realty, traded in the green with Bank, FMCG, Pharma and IT climbing more than a percent each.', 'According to the brokerage, if there are fresh rate cuts or infusion of liquidity by global central banks then FII flows could resume into select emerging markets as and when the covid-19 virus impact fades out.', 'About 1147 shares have advanced, 799 shares declined, and 124 shares are unchanged.', 'Mounting coronavirus cases, exodus by foreign institutional investors, and RBI playing the waiting game to provide stimulus has prompted investors to exit the market.', 'The Sensex closed 61.13 points higher at 38,470.61, and the Nifty was up 18 points at 11,269.', 'Nifty on March 4 slid almost 200 points during the day but witnessed a sharp recovery in the second half of the session.']

News: ['Key support level for the Nifty is placed at 10,201.67, followed by 10,114.43. News: ['Traders should remain neutral and wait for a breakout in either of the directions, Mazhar Mohammad of Chartviewindia.in has said.', 'Top Nifty gainers included IOC, TCS, Infosys, and BPCL.', 'As fundamentals will take time to turn positive, investors should stick to quality largecaps rather than midcaps or smallcaps.', 'While the momentum may continue in the near term, one should be cautious going ahead as the fundamentals continue to be weak and valuations seem to be expensive at around 21x FY20 P/E.', 'Pankaj Pandey, Head of Research at ICICI direct is of the view that the sharper leg of the rally has already happened, riding on economy unlock as well as global markets run-up.', "We believe that market discounts the news in advance and moves ahead of the events and yesterday's movement was a clear indication of the same", 'Banking has seen strong rollover but since momentum remains missing, further consolidation before strong action is seen in this space.', 'On the sectoral front, except FMCG and pharma other indices ended in the green. BSE Midcap and Smallcap indices ended marginally higher.', 'Any negative news flow from the global front or any geopolitical concerns could accelerate the selloff as the second wave of COVID-19 crisis continues to be a concern for India and the world.']

News: ['Key support level for the Nifty is placed at 10,244.67, followed by 10,176.93. If the index moves up, the key resistance levels to watch out for are 10,359.07 and 10,405.73.', 'Top Nifty gainers included HUL, Cipla, Britannia Industries, and HDFC Bank.', 'Mazhar Mohammad of Chartviewindia.in advised traders to avoid short side bets as downside seems to be limited.', 'Currently on the basis of float market capitalisation and other conditions for inclusion, the brokerage expects inclusion of HDFC Life Insurance Company, SBI Life Insurance Company, Divis Labs and Dabur India in the Nifty50 Index.', 'Experts expect the volatility to continue and if the index breaks 10,200 then there could be further selling pressure.', 'We think that this time in July, the index will give the breakout of 10,500-10,550 level with the good support of 10050-10000, afterwards, the target would be at 11,040 levels.', "Segments that will remain under stress for a longer time are hotels, restaurants, malls, airlines, multiplexes, and highly discretionary spending, says Max Life Insurance's Mihir Vora.", 'The strategy would enable the traders to trade the setup with a decent risk-reward.', 'Coal India, Axis Bank, Tech Mahindra, Hindalco Industries and SBI were among major losers on the Nifty, while gainers included HDFC Bank, HUL, Britannia Industries, Cipla and M&M.', "The banking index managed to give a 'cup and handle' pattern breakout by closing above 21,100 and the target, as per the pattern, will reach 24,000 which suggests a bullish movement ahead in mid-term."]

News: ['Key support level for the Nifty is placed at 10,337.4, followed by 10,244.8. If the index moves up, the key resistance levels to watch out for are 10,484.8 and 10,539.6', '"For the time being, it seems traders would do well by focusing on stock specific opportunities rather than initiating positional trades on index," said Mazhar Mohammad of Chartviewindia.in.', 'Top Nifty gainers include names like HDFC, UPL, Bajaj Finserv, and Axis Bank.', "Considering the last six month's average criteria of NSE parameters, the brokerage has short listed 11 stocks for fresh inclusion in the F&O segment.", '"Long term investors should not get carried away by such instant short term outperformance and can have exposure upto 20-25 percent in few promising quality mid & small cap stocks," Prashanth Tapse said.', 'We overall assume FY21 expected earnings will be impacted by the lockdown in first/second quarter and earnings recovery may be visible only from the second half of FY21.', 'In case of Pharma index which rallied over 60 percent from its March lows, Gautam Shah feels charts are good and the trend is rock solid.', 'Equity markets had a plethora of headwinds during the first half of the calendar year 2020. News: ['Sectorally, action was seen in energy, telecom, healthcare, realty, and FMCG stocks while profit-taking was visible in banks, finance and consumer durable stocks.', 'The recovery in the smallcap and midcap stocks has been better in 2020 compared to 2019, as these stocks were beaten down quite a lot and non-institutional participation rose as the momentum picked up.', 'From a technical perspective, the bulls will remain in control if the Nifty records a breakout above 10,900.', 'The Nifty reclaimed 10,800 levels on July 9 but the bulls will only be able to take control once the index breaks above 10,900 levels.', 'Earnings expected to be soft over the next two quarters due to forced lockdown but should recover in the second half as the unlocking of the economy will give some fillip to recovery.', 'Benchmark indices are trading lower in the volatile session. Buying seen in the IT, pharma and FMCG sectors, while bank, metal and auto remained under pressure.', 'The Bank Nifty index has been a laggard in the current upmove and may outperform the broader markets with key potential targets of 23,800-24,100 levels over the next few weeks.']

News: ['Key support level for the Nifty is placed at 10,741.13, followed by 10,679.57. If the index moves up, the key resistance levels to watch out for are 10,879.13 and 10,955.57.', 'The Nifty appears to have witnessed profit booking from its intraday high of 10,894, after opening gap up, as it tested its 200-day simple moving average whose value is placed at 10,885 levels', 'Mazhar Mohammad of Chartviewindia.in advised traders to focus on stock specific opportunities rather than betting on trendless index.', 'The yellow metal could rise towards $1,935/ounce in the next six months of 2020.', 'Long buildup was seen in stocks such as Indiabulls Housing Finance, MindTree, and Bharat Forge.', 'The Nifty would first surpass the 10,850 mark and head towards the 78.6 percent retracement zone of the entire fall i.e. 11,000-11,200, where we can see some profit-booking taking place.', 'The underlying situation in India is not so encouraging and the improvement in the economic scenario has been a bumpy road but still stock markets have recovered much before than expected.', 'In the very short term, as the majority of the momentum indicators are trading in overbought zones, the possibility of small retracement towards 10,500 levels cannot be denied.', 'If someone wants to invest for a long-term wealth creation, ‚ÄòBharat Bond ETF, Rossari Biotech, and Yes Bank IPO are preferred choice filtered on the basis of wealth creation/protection of capital.', 'Experts suggest that a break below 10,650 can lead to further profit-taking, while a break above 10,900 can give strength to the bulls.', 'Data suggests that the bulls are cautious at this juncture and the chance of a further upmove is quite remote.', 'Except banks, other sectoral indices ended in the green. BSE Midcap and Smallcap indices ended flat.', 'Last week, Nifty gyrated in a slender range of merely 160 points. Amid all this, the benchmark index concluded the week with moderate gains of one and half a percent.']
